parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud grinding or rattling noise
vehicle stuck in neutral
unable to shift gears
vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud whining or clucking noise
vehicle vibrates or shakes
difficulty accelerating
rear wheels lock up or fail to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Engine Control Module Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and engine control module can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or hesitates
engine warning light comes on
difficulty accelerating
throttle body fails to respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
transmission slips or fails to engage
difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
the dashboard lights and radio come on after the vehicle is turned off
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the stability control and traction control lights come on
and the vehicle experiences slow acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn
the vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
and the theft security light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause structural damage to the vehicle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The frame of the vehicle rusts and corrodes
causing structural damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
and the transmission fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stability system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake, swerve, or lose control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The stability system warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly brakes or swerves
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brakes shudder or vibrate
and the vehicle's speed reduces suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult to maneuver, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The power steering warning light appears on the dashboard
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and a loud whining or grinding noise is heard from the power steering pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering column lockup can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult to maneuver, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering column becomes stuck or locked
making it difficult to turn the steering wheel
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Stability System Engaged" or "Service Stability System" message appears on the display screen
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side
the brakes engage unexpectedly
and the steering wheel stiffens or locks up.
